
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

zlib DLL
http://www.zlib.net/

    mkdir zlib123-dll
    unzip zlib123-dll.zip -d zlib123-dll
    cd zlib123-dll && sh ../install-zlib.sh

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

libiconv
http://www.gnu.org/software/libiconv/

    # There is a circular dependency  between gettext and libiconv. As
    # suggested  by the  libiconv documentation,  we'll have  to build
    # libiconv, then build gettext and then rebuild libiconv.

    # First time
    cross-configure --disable-nls
    cross-make && cross-make install

    # Second time
    cross-make distclean
    cross-configure && cross-make && cross-make install

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

gettext
http://www.gnu.org/software/gettext/

    # gettext 0.16.1 fails to build with MinGW due to some conflicting
    # macro definitions. This is fixed  in 0.17, but for 0.16.1 you'll
    # have to apply a  patch to gettext-runtime/intl/localename.c that
    # can be downloaded from here:
    #
    #   http://cvs.savannah.gnu.org/viewvc/gettext/gettext-runtime/\
    #   intl/localename.c?root=gettext&r1=1.15&r2=1.16&view=patch

    # Only build DLLs, no tools nor documentation.
    cd gettext-runtime 

    cross-configure --disable-java
    cross-make && cross-make install

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

DirectX development headers
http://www.libsdl.org/extras/win32/common/

    # These  are  not  strictly  necessary. However,  making  SDL  use
    # DirectSound significantly  reduces audio latency which  seems to
    # be unreasonably high with WaveOut.
    tar -xzf directx-devel.tar.gz -C ~/mingw

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

SDL
http://www.libsdl.org/

     cross-configure && cross-make && cross-make install

